  "slug": "cookies-and-cream-truffles",
  "title": "Cookies and cream truffles",
  "subtitle": "Chocolate sandwich biscuits blitzed with cream cheese, rolled, dipped in white chocolate.",
  "excerpt": "Cookies and cream truffles. A baking recipe from Rebecca's collection, straightforward, reliable, worth weighing rather than scooping.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook, a recipe she's made many times in her own kitchen.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cookies and cream truffles. A British home-cook's dish, the kind of recipe families adjust across generations. Adjustable for what you need.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cookies bake fast and reward a chilled dough. Pull them out when the edges set and the middles still look slightly underdone.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Chocolate sandwich biscuit",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 454,
              "prepNote": "3 sleeves",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp5pghox0003zcv4ot0jgimz",
              "ingredientSlug": "chocolate-sandwich-biscuit"
            },
            {
              "name": "Cream cheese",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 227,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3ou001brkv4f03ko2ao",
              "ingredientSlug": "cream-cheese"
            },
            {
              "name": "Vanilla extract",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": "using different extracts allows for subtle flavour changes...I've used mint extract, upped to 1 tsp",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f97x00b3rkv4kdhng3ak",
              "ingredientSlug": "vanilla-extract"
            },
            {
              "name": "Milk chocolate",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 454,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f96800b0rkv4y47rb9zt",
              "ingredientSlug": "milk-chocolate"
            },
            {
              "name": "White chocolate",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f96t00b1rkv4pgl2dt11",
              "ingredientSlug": "white-chocolate"
            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Using a food processor, grind cookies to a fine powder.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "With a mixer, blend cookie powder, cream cheese and vanilla extract until thoroughly mixed (there should be no white traces of cream cheese).",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Roll into small balls and place on a wax-lined cookie sheet.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Refrigerate for 45 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Line two cookie sheets with wax paper.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "In a double-boiler, melt milk chocolate.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Dip balls and coat thoroughly.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "With slotted spoon, lift balls out of chocolate and let excess chocolate drip off.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Place on a wax-paper-lined cookie sheet.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "In a separate double boiler, melt white chocolate.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Using a fork, drizzle white chocolate over balls.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Let cool.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Store in an airtight container, in the refrigerator.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Or skip the white chocolate drizzle. Instead, sprinkle cookie crumbs on top before the milk chocolate sets, or roll the dipped balls in crumbs.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Use a sugar thermometer. Stages: soft-ball 115°C, hard-ball 125°C, soft-crack 135°C, hard-crack 150°C. Cold-water tests work but the thermometer doesn't lie.",
              "cause": "Sugar didn't reach the right stage, or temperature was guessed.",
              "symptom": "Mixture won't set"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Don't stir once the sugar is dissolved. Brush the inside of the pan with a wet pastry brush to wash crystals down.",
              "cause": "Mixture stirred after it started bubbling, or a stray crystal landed on the side of the pan.",
              "symptom": "Sugar crystallised"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Cool to 43°C before beating. The mixture turns from glossy to matte when ready to set.",
              "cause": "Beaten too soon. While still too hot.",
              "symptom": "Fudge is grainy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Add a teaspoon of warm cream or water and stir until smooth, this is the trick. Drier seizing needs more liquid; thin seizing wants less.",
              "cause": "Water touched melted chocolate.",
              "symptom": "Mixture seized into a ball"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Flavoured version: stir in a teaspoon of vanilla, almond, or peppermint extract once the mixture is off the heat.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Dip-coated: once set, dip pieces in melted dark chocolate and let drip on baking paper.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
